«c2»«ac»COMPARADE PARTY INVITATION«»
«»
«»
«c6»«ac»
What is the ComParade?«»
«»
«c7»«as»The ComParade is a computer scene party. In contrast to so-called LAN parties, 
we focus on creativity. In Competitions, programmers, graphics artists and 
musicians compete (hence the name) for the applause of the audience. Other 
prominent scene parties are the Danish The Party or the Assembly.«»
«»
«»
«c6»«ac»
What's special about the ComParade?«»
«»
«c7»«as»Our focus are interesting competitions. We don't have an MP3 Music
competition because we all have better techno tracks at home. Instead, we'll be 
holding a Four channel tracker music competition, where all entries need to 
be written using one of the ...Tracker programs (NoiseTracker, StarTrekker, 
ProTracker) and must not have more than four channels.«»
«»
Also, we will not allow violent computer games. If we did, we could not allow 
minors at the party, also we had bad experiences with some hardcore gamers 
feeling annoyed by our competitions. So if you want to play games, you should 
go to a LAN party instead.«»
«c6»«ac»
When will ComParade take place?«»
«»
«c7»«as»The party will take place from 
February 8th to 10th 2002 somewhere in the Munich area (we don't have exact details 
since we need to have a rough estimate on the number of visitors first before 
we decide).«»
«»
«»
